The paper deals with geometric graphs and their properties, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of spanning ratio and competitiveness also suggests that it could belong to the data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The paper also presents partial orders and bounds, which are common in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
